<refnamediv>
  <refname>stalonetray</refname>
  <refpurpose><emphasis>sta</emphasis>nd-<emphasis>alone</emphasis>
  system tray (notification area) implementation. This document covers
  @VERSION_STR@ version of stalonetray.</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
  <cmdsynopsis>
  <command>stalonetray</command>
  <arg rep="repeat"><replaceable>option</replaceable></arg>
  </cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>DESCRIPTION</title>

  <para>Stalonetray is a stand-alone system tray (notification area)
  for X Window System/X11 (e.g. XOrg or XFree86). It has minimal build
  and run-time dependencies: an X11 lib only. Complete
  <abbrev>XEMBED</abbrev> support is under development. Stalonetray
  works with virtually any <abbrev>EWMH</abbrev>-compliant window
  manager.</para>

  <para>The behaviour and the look of stalonetray can be configured either via
  command line options or via configuration file. As usual, command-line options
  have precedence over options that are specified in the configuration
  file.</para>

  <para>Names of command line parameter may have two variants: short
  (<option>&ndash;o</option>) and long (<option>&ndash;&ndash;option</option>).
  Write <option>&ndash;o</option><replaceable>value</replaceable> or
  <option>&ndash;o</option> <replaceable>value</replaceable> to pass a value
  using the short name of a parameter; to pass a value using a long name, write
  <option>&ndash;&ndash;option</option> <replaceable>value</replaceable> or
  <option>&ndash;&ndash;option</option>=<replaceable>value</replaceable>. All
  flag-like parameters have optional boolean value that when ommited is assumed
  to be "true". Write "true", "yes", "1", for positive boolean values, and
  "false", "no", "0" for negative ones. <emphasis>Please note, that a value
  cannot start with "-". This limitation is to be fixed in future
  releases.</emphasis> </para>
  
  <para>Default configuration file is <filename>$HOME/.stalonetrayrc</filename>.
  A configuration file contains case-insensetive keyword-argument pairs, one per
  line. Lines starting with '#' and empty lines are ignored.  Alternatively,
  confiuration file can specified via <option>&ndash;c</option> or
  <option>&ndash;&ndash;config</option> command-line options.</para>
 
  <para>Below is the list of possible command line/configuration file options.
  Options starting with hyphens are command-line parameters others are
  configuration file keywords.  Options that are new in @VERSION_STR@ version
  are marked with "NEW in @VERSION_STR@". </para>
  
</refsect1>
<refsect1 id="opt">
  <title>OPTIONS</title>

  <variablelist>
  
  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;display</option> <replaceable>display</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>display</option> <replaceable>display</replaceable>
  </term>
  <listitem><para>Use X display <replaceable>display</replaceable>.</para></listitem> 
  </varlistentry>
  
  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;dbg&ndash;level</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>dbg_level</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para>Set the level of debug output to
  <replaceable>n</replaceable> (stalonetray must be compiled with
  <option>&ndash;&ndash;enable&ndash;debug</option> for this option to have
  effect.) Default value: <userinput>4</userinput>.</para></listitem> 
  </varlistentry>
  
  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;bg</option> <replaceable>color</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;background</option> <replaceable>color</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>background</option> <replaceable>color</replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para>Use <replaceable>color</replaceable> for tray`s background.
  <replaceable>color</replaceable> can be specified as an <abbrev>HTML</abbrev> hex triplet or
  as a name from rgb.txt (note that '#' must be quoted). Default value: <userinput>#777777</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  
  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;c</option> <replaceable>filename</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;config</option> <replaceable>filename</replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para>Read configuration from
  <replaceable>filename</replaceable> instead of default
  <filename>$HOME/.stalonetrayrc</filename>.</para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;d</option> <replaceable>decspec</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;decorations</option> <replaceable>decspec</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>decorations</option> <replaceable>decspec</replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para>Specify visiblie tray window decorations. Possible values for
  <replaceable>decspec</replaceable> are: <userinput>all</userinput>,
  <userinput>title</userinput>, <userinput>border</userinput>,
  <userinput>none</userinput> (default). This
  option is NEW in 0.7 and replaces now deprecated <option>no_deco</option>,
  <option>no_title</option>, and <option>no_border</option> options.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;f</option> <optional><replaceable>level</replaceable></optional></term>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;fuzzy-edges</option> <optional><replaceable>level</replaceable></optional></term>
  <term><option>fuzzy_edges</option> <optional><replaceable>level</replaceable></optional></term>
  <listitem><para>Enable fuzzy edges of tray window and sets fuzziness level.
  (NEW in 0.7); <replaceable>level</replaceable> ranges from
  <userinput>0</userinput> (disabled, default) to <userinput>3</userinput>.
  When ommited, <replaceable>level</replaceable> defaults to 2.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;geometry</option> <replaceable>geometry_spec</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>geometry</option> <replaceable>geometry_spec</replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para>Set tray`s initial geometry to <replaceable>geometry_spec</replaceable>,
  specified in standard X notation: 
  <replaceable>width</replaceable>x<replaceable>height</replaceable>[+<replaceable>x</replaceable>[+<replaceable>y</replaceable>]].
  Default value: <userinput>124x24+0-0</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry> 
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;grow&ndash;gravity</option>
  <replaceable>gravity</replaceable></term> <term><option>grow_gravity</option>
  <replaceable>gravity</replaceable></term> <listitem><para>Specify icon
  positioning gravity (one of <userinput>N</userinput>,
  <userinput>S</userinput>, <userinput>W</userinput>, <userinput>E</userinput>,
  <userinput>NW</userinput>, <userinput>NE</userinput>,
  <userinput>SW</userinput>, <userinput>SE</userinput>). Grow gravity specifies
  directions in which tray may and will grow.  For instance, if you specify
  <userinput>W</userinput>, tray will be allowed to grow to the left (oppisite
  to West) side only; <userinput>NW</userinput> will allow tray to grow down
  and to the right (these are sides, that are opposite to upper-left, or
  North-West, corner). Default value: <userinput>NE</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;icon&ndash;gravity</option> <replaceable>gravity</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>icon_gravity</option> <replaceable>gravity</replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para>Specify icon positioning gravity (one of <userinput>NW</userinput>,
  <userinput>NE</userinput>, <userinput>SW</userinput>, <userinput>SE</userinput>). If you specify,
  for instance, <userinput>SW</userinput>, icons will appear starting from the lower-left corner
  of stalonetray window. Default value: <userinput>NE</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;i</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;icon&ndash;size</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>icon_size</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para>Set basic icon size to <replaceable>n</replaceable>.
  Default value: <userinput>24</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;ignore&ndash;icon&ndash;resize</option></term>
  <term><option>ignore_icon_resize <optional><replaceable>bool</replaceable></optional></option></term>
  <listitem><para>Ignore icon resizing events, effectively forcing all icons dimensions
  to be icon_size x icon_size. Default value: <userinput>false</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;h</option></term>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;help</option></term>
  <listitem><para>Show help message.</para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;max&ndash;width</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>max_width</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para>Set tray`s maximal width to <replaceable>n</replaceable> 
  (0 means no limit). Default value: <userinput>0</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;max&ndash;height</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>max_height</option> <replaceable>n</replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para>Set tray`s maximal height to <replaceable>n</replaceable> 
  (0 means no limit). Default value: <userinput>0</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;no&ndash;shrink</option></term>
  <term><option>no_shrink</option> <optional><replaceable>bool</replaceable></optional></term>
  <listitem><para>Do not shrink tray window back after icon removal. Useful when
  tray is swallowed by another window like FvwmButtons. Default value: <userinput>false</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;p</option></term>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;parent&ndash;bg</option></term>
  <term><option>parent_bg</option> <optional><replaceable>bool</replaceable></optional></term>
  <listitem><para>Use parent for background. Default value: <userinput>false</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;pixmap&ndash;bg <replaceable>path_to_xpm</replaceable></option></term>
  <term><option>pixmap_bg</option> <replaceable>path_to_xpm</replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para>Use pixmap from an XPM file specified by <replaceable>path_to_xpm</replaceable> for 
  tray`s background (pixmap will be tiled to fill the whole window).
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

<!--  <varlistentry> -->
<!--  <term><option> &ndash;&ndash;permanent</option></term> -->
<!--  <term><option>permanent</option> <arg><replaceable>bool</replaceable></arg></term> -->
<!--  <listitem><para>Reacquire tray selection after loss.</para></listitem> -->
<!--  </varlistentry> -->

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;respect&ndash;icon&ndash;hints</option></term>
  <term><option>respect_icon_hints</option> <optional><replaceable>bool</replaceable></optional></term>
  <listitem><para>Do respect icon window min_width/min_height size hints. This may help with unusually-sized icons, which fail
  to resize themselves after being resized to icon_size x icon_size. Note, that if stalonetray is configured to ignore icon resize events, this 
  option has no effect. Default value: <userinput>false</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;skip&ndash;taskbar</option></term>
  <term><option>skip_taskbar</option> <optional><replaceable>bool</replaceable></optional></term>
  <listitem><para>Hide tray`s window from the taskbar. Default value:
  <userinput>false</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;sticky</option></term>
  <term><option>sticky</option> <optional><replaceable>bool</replaceable></optional></term>
  <listitem><para>Make tray`s window sticky across multiple desktops/pages.
  Default value: <userinput>false</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;tint&ndash;color</option></term>
  <term><option>tint_color</option> <optional><replaceable>bool</replaceable></optional></term>
  <listitem><para>Set tinting color. Default value:
  <userinput>white</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;tint&ndash;value</option></term>
  <term><option>tint_color</option> <optional><replaceable>bool</replaceable></optional></term>
  <listitem><para>Set tinting level. Default value: <userinput>0</userinput>
  (tinting disabled).
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;t</option></term>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;transparent</option></term>
  <term><option>transparent</option> <optional><replaceable>bool</replaceable></optional></term>
  <listitem><para>Enable root transparency. Default value:
  <userinput>false</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;v</option></term>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;vertical</option></term>
  <term><option>vertical</option> <optional><replaceable>bool</replaceable></optional></term>
  <listitem><para>Use vertical layout of icons (horizontal is used by default).</para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;window-layer</option> <replaceable>layer</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>window_layer</option> <replaceable>layer</replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para>Sets the <abbrev>EWMH</abbrev>&ndash;compliant layer of tray`s window. Possible values for <replaceable>layer</replaceable>: 
  <userinput>bottom</userinput>, <userinput>normal</userinput>, <userinput>top</userinput>. Default value: <userinput>normal</userinput>.
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;window-type</option> <replaceable>type</replaceable></term>
  <term><option>window_type</option> <replaceable>type</replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para>Sets the <abbrev>EWMH</abbrev>&ndash;compliant type of tray`s window. Possible values for <replaceable>type</replaceable>: 
  <userinput>dock</userinput>, <userinput>normal</userinput>, <userinput>toolbar</userinput>,
  <userinput>utility</userinput>. Default value: <userinput>dock</userinput>.</para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;w</option></term>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;withdrawn</option></term>
  <term><option>withdrawn</option> <optional><replaceable>bool</replaceable></optional></term>
  <listitem><para>Start in withdrawn (dockapp) mode. NEW in 0.7, prior to that
  was default mode.</para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>&ndash;&ndash;xsync</option></term>
  <term><option>xsync</option> <optional><replaceable>bool</replaceable></optional></term>
  <listitem><para>Operate on X server synchronously (<emphasis>SLOW</emphasis>, turned off by default).
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>
<!--
  <varlistentry>
  <term><option></option> <replaceable></replaceable></term>
  <listitem><para><replaceable></replaceable>
  </para></listitem>
  </varlistentry>
-->
  </variablelist>
</refsect1>
<refsect1>
<title>FILES</title>
<para><filename>$HOME/.stalonetrayrc</filename> &mdash; default configuration file.</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1>
<title>BUGS</title>
<para>There are some, definetly.</para>

<para>If you have found a bug, please try to reproduce it with debug level set to 8
and send the log file to me: <email>busa_ru@users.sourceforge.net</email>. If
you need support, the best way to get it is also to e&ndash;mail me directly. If
you have installed stalonetray from distribution repository, you can also file a
bug there.</para>
</refsect1>
